    'announcements' => 
    array (
      'en' => 
      array (
        'format' => 'html',
        'content' => 'The PHP development team is proud to announce the immediate availability of PHP [5.5.0](http://php.net/downloads.php#v5.5.0). This release includes a large number of new features and bug fixes.

**The key features of PHP 5.5.0 include:**

- Added [generators](http://php.net/generators) and coroutines.
- Added the [finally](http://php.net/exceptions) keyword.
- Added a [simplified password hashing API](http://php.net/password).
- Added [support for constant array/string dereferencing](http://php.net/migration55.new-features#migration55.new-features.const-dereferencing).
- Added scalar class name resolution via [::class](http://php.net/oop5.basic#language.oop5.basic.class.class).
- Added [support for using empty() on the result of function calls and other expressions](http://php.net/migration55.new-features#migration55.new-features.empty).
- Added [support for non-scalar Iterator keys in foreach](http://php.net/migration55.new-features#migration55.new-features.non-scalar-iterator-keys).
- Added [support for list() constructs in foreach statements](http://php.net/foreach#control-structures.foreach.list).
- Added the [Zend OPcache](http://php.net/opcache) extension for opcode caching.
- The GD library has been upgraded to version 2.1 adding new functions and improving existing functionality.
- A lot more improvements and fixes.

**Changes that affect compatibility:**

- [PHP logo GUIDs](http://php.net/php_logo_guid) have been removed.
- Windows XP and 2003 support dropped.
- Case insensitivity is no longer locale specific. All case insensitive matching for function, class and constant names is now performed in a locale independent manner according to ASCII rules.

For users upgrading from PHP 5.4, [a migration guide is available](http://php.net/migration55)detailing the changes between 5.4 and 5.5.0.

 For a full list of changes in PHP 5.5.0, see the [ChangeLog](http://php.net/ChangeLog-5.php#5.5.0).',
